THE King's Theatre, Glasgow, has released 50 special charity tickets for its 50th panto year. Panto tickets to help kids THE King's Theatre, Glasgow, has released 50 special charity tickets for its 50th panto year.The tickets for Peter Pan on December 11 cost &pound;50 and 40% of the price will be donated to Yorkhill Children's Charity.Manager James Haworth said they wanted to do something &quot;extra special&quot;. 